Packaging NsCDE

If someone wants to make own Debian, RPM or Arch package, or as a template
for distribution package, this directory contains workable files for that
task.

** Chinese Localization Version (v2.3_zh) **

This version includes full Chinese (zh) translation support with 25 translation
files. The build system has been fixed to properly compile and install Chinese
locales.

Repository: https://github.com/wenyinos/NsCDE-zh

1. Debian, Ubuntu, MX Linux and friends

- Obtain NsCDE-zh as a tarball release (v2.3_zh) or clone master branch from Github.

- Make some build directory:

  mkdir build
  cd build

- Move the content of NsCDE-zh release or master branch to it

  mv ~/NsCDE-zh nscde-zh-v2.3_zh
  cd nscde-zh-v2.3_zh

- Symlink debian build environment into top directory

  ln -s pkg/debian

- Make sure you have devscripts, gcc, autoconf, automake and
  NsCDE build time dependencies (see debian/control)

  apt install devscripts

- Build a package

  debuild -uc -us -b

- The result will be in the parent directory. Install it.

  cd ..
  sudo -i || su -
  dpkg -i ./nscde-zh_v2.3.2_zh-1_<arch>.deb

That's it.


2. Red Hat, CentOS, Fedora, Open SuSE and similar:

- Obtain NsCDE-zh as a tarball release (v2.3_zh).

- Optional step: if installing from the git master branch
  instead of release tarball, make a tarball prior to building:

  mv NsCDE-zh NsCDE-zh-v2.3_zh
  tar cpzf NsCDE-zh-v2.3_zh.tar.gz NsCDE-zh-v2.3_zh

- Make sure you have rpm-build, gcc, autoconf, automake installed

  yum|zypper|dnf install rpm-build

- Instruct rpmbuild to find spec file in the tarball and use it:

  rpmbuild -tb NsCDE-zh-v2.3_zh.tar.gz

- Install it:

  sudo -i || su -
  rpm -i NsCDE-zh-v2.3-3.zh.<arch>.rpm


3. Arch Linux (and probably compatible packaging distros?)

- Obtain NsCDE-zh as a tarball release (v2.3_zh) or clone master branch from Github.

- Make some build directory:

  mkdir build
  cd build

- Move the content of NsCDE-zh release or master branch to it

  mv ~/NsCDE-zh nscde-zh-v2.3_zh
  or
  tar xzf ~/NsCDE-zh-v2.3_zh.tar.gz
  mv NsCDE-zh-v2.3_zh nscde-zh-v2.3_zh

- Pull out PKGBUILD file

  cp nscde-zh-v2.3_zh/pkg/pacman/PKGBUILD .

- Make a new tarball:

  tar cpzf nscde-zh-v2.3_zh.tar.gz nscde-zh-v2.3_zh

- Build a package

   makepkg

Install the package:

   sudo -i || su -
   pacman -U /home/user/build/nscde-zh-v2.3-3.zh-<arch>.pkg.tar.zst

